CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 25, 1953, pg. 2, reads: "At Southwest PTA Conference - The Southwestern Pennsylvania Conference of Parent Teacher Association was held at the William Penn Hotel last Saturday. Shown during the sessions are, middle photo: Dr. Clara E. Cockerille, assistant superintendent of schools of Armstrong County, who spoke at the morning session on "Meeting the Needs of Children and Youth," is shown chatting with Mrs. Alexander J. Allen, who led the morning devotions...Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Clara E. Cockerille talking to Mrs. Alexander J. Allen in William Penn Hotel for PTA Conference
